{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:30:26.444151+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 687bd3e88db7dfe057ebf64412e9de4a40d7b35b)", "id": "lc_dd30c5a7-2d85-417d-bbdb-f42f8013d1bb"}, {"type": "text", "text": "import axios from 'axios'\nimport { ElMessageBox, ElMessage } from 'element-plus'\nimport store from '@/store'\nimport { getToken } from '@/utils/auth'\n\n// create an axios instance\nconst service = axios.create({\n  baseURL: process.env.VUE_APP_BASE_API, // url = base url + request url\n  // withCredentials: true, // send cookies when cross-domain requests\n  timeout: 5000, // request timeout\n})\n\n// request interceptor\nservice.interceptors.request.use(\n  (config) => {\n    // do something before request is sent\n\n    if (store.getters.token) {\n      // let each request carry token\n      // ['X-Token'] is a custom headers key\n      // please modify it according to the actual situation\n      config.headers['X-Token'] = getToken()\n    }\n    return config\n  },\n  (error) => {\n    // do something with request error\n    console.log(error) // for debug\n    return Promise.reject(error)\n  }\n)\n\n// response interceptor\nservice.interceptors.response.use(\n  /**\n   * If you want to get http information such as headers or status\n   * Please return  response => response\n   */\n\n  /**\n   * Determine the request status by custom code\n   * Here is just an example\n   * You can also judge the status by HTTP Status Code\n   */\n  (response) => {\n    const res = response.data\n\n    // if the custom code is not 20000, it is judged as an error.\n    if (res.code !== 20000) {\n      ElMessage({\n        message: res.message || 'Error',\n        type: 'error',\n        duration: 5 * 1000,\n      })\n\n      // 50008: Illegal token; 50012: Other clients logged in; 50014: Token expired;\n      if (res.code === 50008 || res.code === 50012 || res.code === 50014) {\n        // to re-login\n        ElMessageBox.confirm(\n          '您已登出，可以取消停留在此页面上，或者再次登录',\n          '重新登录',\n          {\n            confirmButtonText: '重新登录',\n            cancelButtonText: '离开',\n            type: 'warning',\n          }\n        ).then(() => {\n          store.dispatch('user/resetToken').then(() => {\n            location.reload()\n          })\n        })\n      }\n      return Promise.reject(new Error(res.message || 'Error'))\n    } else {\n      return res\n    }\n  },\n  (error) => {\n    console.log('err' + error) // for debug\n    ElMessage({\n      message: error.message,\n      type: 'error',\n      duration: 5 * 1000,\n    })\n    return Promise.reject(error)\n  }\n)\n\nexport default service\n", "id": "lc_032a83da-ee32-48c1-a2f1-5b69fba7cc58"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "47e98633-578f-4124-bf84-96a067c30813", "tool_call_id": "call_8f42b29cc30b4a40af2c88b1", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:30:26.486932+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 050442fab01646f6bfe0285ef981bdba071e0d4b)", "id": "lc_5b7f1cab-dbe0-41f5-a360-3604fed0a705"}, {"type": "text", "text": "import request from '@/utils/request'\n\nexport function login(data) {\n  return request({\n    url: '/vue-admin-template/user/login',\n    method: 'post',\n    data,\n  })\n}\n\nexport function getInfo(token) {\n  return request({\n    url: '/vue-admin-template/user/info',\n    method: 'get',\n    params: { token },\n  })\n}\n\nexport function logout() {\n  return request({\n    url: '/vue-admin-template/user/logout',\n    method: 'post',\n  })\n}\n", "id": "lc_abd9fa5a-e3fa-42ee-a4de-8354a49d402a"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "af0099cb-564b-4640-8928-82779efdbb8e", "tool_call_id": "call_b0795bd87d1942b9b7eacd24", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:30:40.003285+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## How the Template Switches Between Development and Production API Base Paths\n\n### Mechanism: Vue CLI Environment Files\n\nThe template uses **`.env.*` files** at the project root, each defining a `VUE_APP_BASE_API` variable:\n\n| Environment File | `VUE_APP_BASE_API` | `NODE_ENV` |\n|---|---|---|\n| `.env.development` | `/dev-api` | *(implicit development)* |\n| `.env.production` | `/prod-api` | *(implicit production)* |\n| `.env.staging` | `/stage-api` | `production` |\n\nVue CLI automatically loads the appropriate file based on the command (`npm run dev`, `npm run build`, etc.). Because the variable is prefixed with `VUE_APP_`, it's exposed to client-side code via `process.env.VUE_APP_BASE_API`.\n\n### How It's Consumed\n\nIn **`src/utils/request.js`**, an Axios instance is created with the env variable as its `baseURL`:\n\n```js\nconst service = axios.create({\n  baseURL: process.env.VUE_APP_BASE_API,\n  timeout: 5000,\n})\n```\n\n### The Dev/Prod Split in Practice\n\n- **Development** (`npm run dev`): The `baseURL` is `/dev-api`. Meanwhile, `vue.config.js` wires up a **mock server** via `devServer.before: require('./mock/mock-server.js')`, which intercepts requests matching mock routes before they leave the machine. So `/dev-api/vue-admin-template/user/login` is handled entirely by the local mock.\n- **Production** (`npm run build`): The `baseURL` becomes `/prod-api` (or `/stage-api` for staging), and requests go to a real backend — no mock server is attached.\n\nAdditionally, `vue.config.js` uses `isDev` (`process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development'`) to conditionally set `publicPath` (`/` in dev, `/vue3-admin-template/` in prod), enable source maps, and configure Webpack code-splitting only for production.\n\n---\n\n### Mock Login Usernames and Tokens\n\nFrom **`mock/user.js`**, there are exactly **two** mock usernames:\n\n| Username | Token |\n|---|---|\n| `admin` | `admin-token` |\n| `editor` | `editor-token` |\n\nThe mock login handler looks up the submitted `username` in a `tokens` map. If the username is `admin`, the response is `{ code: 20000, data: { token: 'admin-token' } }`. If it's `editor`, the token is `editor-token`. Any other username returns error code 60204 (\"Account and password are incorrect\").\n\nEach token then resolves to specific user info (roles, name, introduction, avatar) via the `users` map in the same file, which is consumed by the mock `/vue-admin-template/user/info` endpoint.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1214, "prompt_tokens": 12343, "total_tokens": 13557, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 599, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 11392, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0005049576, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001650376, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00033992}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780871426-ZyJXoPOa9SLzWY9mFxSv", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea435-71b8-7872-8d6c-d44d290f16a5-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 12343, "output_tokens": 1214, "total_tokens": 13557, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 11392}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 599}}}}]}}}
